  "prompt": "Why is \"The Awakening\" banned?",
  "response": "Kate Chopin's novel \"The Awakening\" has faced censorship and criticism since its publication in 1899 primarily because of its controversial themes, including:\n\n1. Female sexuality and sexual desire\n2. Challenging traditional gender roles and marriage expectations\n3. A woman's exploration of personal independence and self-discovery\n4. Questioning societal norms about women's behavior\n5. The protagonist's eventual suicide, which was seen as immoral\n\nThe book was considered scandalous for its time, as it portrayed a woman who sought personal fulfillment outside of her traditional roles as wife and mother. While it is not universally banned today, it has been challenged in some schools and libraries over the years due to its mature themes and perceived inappropriate content.",
